# Custom Cursor Rules for Food Calorie Analyzer

## Coding Standards
- Use Swift 5.0 syntax and features.
- Follow MVVM architecture for all views and view models.
- Use SwiftUI for UI components.
- Ensure all files are included in the main app target.

## Best Practices
- Write clear, descriptive commit messages for each feature or fix.
- Use meaningful variable and function names.
- Comment complex logic for clarity.
- Ensure error handling is robust and user-friendly.

## Testing
- Test all features on both simulator and real devices.
- Use SweetPad for simulator testing.
- Ensure all UI elements are responsive and functional.

## Documentation
- Keep README.md updated with installation and build steps.
- Document API integration and data models in instruction.md.
- Use .cursor-rules to enforce coding standards. 